Class ActiveArray

java.lang.Object
  org.mundo.rt.TypedContainer
      org.mundo.rt.ActiveArray
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Object>, java.util.Collection<java.lang.Object>, java.util.List<java.lang.Object>
public class ActiveArray
extends TypedContainer
implements java.util.List<java.lang.Object>

TypedArray is a list class that provides access methods for boxing/unboxing of base types.

Author:
Erwin Aitenbichler

toArray

public <T> T[] toArray(T[] a)
Returns an array containing all of the elems in this list in the correct order; the runtime type of the returned array is that of the specified array. If the list fits in the specified array, it is returned therein. Otherwise, a new array is allocated with the runtime type of the specified array and the size of this list.

Specified by:
toArray in interface java.util.Collection<java.lang.Object>
Specified by:
toArray in interface java.util.List<java.lang.Object>
Parameters:
a - the array into which the elems of the list are to be stored, if it is big enough; otherwise, a new array of the same runtime type is allocated for this purpose.
Throws:
java.lang.ArrayStoreException - if the runtime type of a is not a supertype of the runtime type of every element in this list.
